Infosys, Rural Electrification, State Bank: India Equity Preview

-- B y   U n n i   K r i s h n a n
-- 
2011-05-25T01:36:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/infosys-rural-electrification-state-bank-india-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in  India  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the last close.  The Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive Index, or Sensex,
gained 18.64, or 0.1 percent, to 18,011.97. The S&P CNX Nifty
Index on the National Stock Exchange rose 0.2 percent to
5,394.85. The BSE 200 Index increased 0.2 percent to 2,226.40.  Infosys Technologies Ltd. (INFO)  : India’s second-largest
software exporter said it received a subpoena from a U.S. court
in  Texas  seeking documents related to the company’s use of B1
business visas, according to a statement on the Bombay Stock
Exchange. The shares rose 0.3 percent to 2,844.5 rupees.  Rural Electrification Corp. (RECL IN): India’s state-
controlled lender to power projects expects to get approval this
week from India’s central bank to borrow $750 million overseas,
Chairman H.D. Khunteta said by telephone from  New Delhi . The
company said it increased profit 28 percent to 25.8 billion
rupees ($571 million) in the year ended March 31. The shares
fell 1.4 percent to 202.35 rupees.  State Bank  of India (SBIN IN): Net interest margins at the
nation’s largest lender will widen and help turn around the
business, Chairman Pratip Chaudhuri said in an interview. The
shares fell 1.2 percent 2,222.1 rupees.  To contact the reporters on this story:
